textBeforeTable: Overbought_YTD Here are other names that had phenomenal runs this year but are now pulling back. Some Wall Street darlings, including Facebook, Netflix, Priceline and Yahoo, are down over 8 percent for the week. Biotech is also getting hammered. The NYSE Arca Biotech Index fell by 4.5 percent on Tuesday—its worst percentage drop in two years. One reason for the sharp decline is that these stocks have been hot performers, with S&P 500 biotech companies up about 60 percent in 2013. Other major indexes are also feeling the heat. The Nasdaq 100 has fallen 2.7 percent in the past two days, its worst two-day loss in over three months, while the Dow is off by 930 points, or 6 percent, from its all-time high of 15,709.58 in September. Case in point: Vertex Pharmaceuticals. The stock gained more than 90 percent before pulling back almost 20 percent from its 52-week high. While investors have benefited handsomely year-to-date, some of those gains are evaporating.
